<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <title>Technical Presentation – F1 Project</title>
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <style>
        :root {
            --bg: #050816;
            --card: #0f172a;
            --accent: #e10600;
            --text: #e5e7eb;
            --muted: #9ca3af;
            --code-bg: #020617;
        }

        * {
            box-sizing: border-box;
        }

        body {
            margin: 0;
            font-family: system-ui, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, "Segoe UI", sans-serif;
            background: radial-gradient(circle at top, #111827 0, #020617 45%, #000 100%);
            color: var(--text);
            line-height: 1.6;
        }

        .wrapper {
            max-width: 960px;
            margin: 0 auto;
            padding: 2.5rem 1.5rem 3.5rem;
        }

        header {
            text-align: center;
            margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
        }

        header h1 {
            font-size: 2.2rem;
            margin: 0 0 0.5rem;
            letter-spacing: 0.06em;
            text-transform: uppercase;
        }

        header p {
            margin: 0.15rem 0;
            color: var(--muted);
            font-size: 0.95rem;
        }

        .tagline {
            margin-top: 0.8rem;
            font-style: italic;
            color: #f9fafb;
        }

        .grid {
            display: grid;
            grid-template-columns: minmax(0, 1.6fr) minmax(0, 1.1fr);
            gap: 1.5rem;
        }

        @media (max-width: 800px) {
            .grid {
                grid-template-columns: 1fr;
            }
        }

        section {
            background: linear-gradient(145deg, rgba(15,23,42,0.96), rgba(15,23,42,0.85));
            border-radius: 14px;
            padding: 1.4rem 1.5rem 1.3rem;
            border: 1px solid rgba(148,163,184,0.25);
            box-shadow: 0 18px 45px rgba(0,0,0,0.55);
            margin-bottom: 1.2rem;
        }

        section h2 {
            margin: 0 0 0.6rem;
            font-size: 1.1rem;
            text-transform: uppercase;
            letter-spacing: 0.12em;
            color: #f9fafb;
        }

        section h3 {
            margin: 0.8rem 0 0.3rem;
            font-size: 0.98rem;
            color: #e5e7eb;
        }

        p {
            margin: 0.25rem 0;
            font-size: 0.95rem;
        }

        ul {
            margin: 0.25rem 0 0.25rem 1.1rem;
            padding: 0;
            font-size: 0.95rem;
        }

        li {
            margin: 0.15rem 0;
        }

        .pill {
            display: inline-block;
            padding: 0.18rem 0.55rem;
            border-radius: 999px;
            border: 1px solid rgba(148,163,184,0.6);
            font-size: 0.78rem;
            text-transform: uppercase;
            letter-spacing: 0.12em;
            color: var(--muted);
            margin-right: 0.35rem;
            margin-bottom: 0.25rem;
        }

        .pill--accent {
            border-color: var(--accent);
            color: #fecaca;
        }

        .code {
            font-family: "JetBrains Mono", ui-monospace, SFMono-Regular, Menlo, Monaco, Consolas, "Liberation Mono", "Courier New", monospace;
            background: var(--code-bg);
            border-radius: 8px;
            padding: 0.6rem 0.7rem;
            font-size: 0.85rem;
            border: 1px solid rgba(148,163,184,0.35);
            overflow-x: auto;
            margin: 0.35rem 0;
        }

        a {
            color: #f97373;
            text-decoration: none;
        }

        a:hover {
            text-decoration: underline;
        }

        .highlight {
            color: #fbbf24;
        }

        footer {
            margin-top: 2rem;
            text-align: center;
            font-size: 0.8rem;
            color: var(--muted);
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
<div class="wrapper">
    <header>
        <h1>F1 Project – Technical Presentation</h1>
        <p>Author: Elisa</p>
        <p>Course: Web Technologies – Final Project</p>
        <p class="tagline">A static Formula 1 themed website built with semantic HTML and modern CSS.</p>
    </header>

    <div class="grid">
        <!-- LEFT COLUMN -->
        <div>
            <section>
                <h2>1. Project overview</h2>
                <p>
                    The project is a static website dedicated to <span class="highlight">Formula 1</span>, 
                    focusing on teams, drivers and key figures of the sport.  
                    The goal is to demonstrate a clean structure, consistent layout and responsive design using only
                    <strong>HTML</strong> and <strong>CSS</strong>.
                </p>
                <p>
                    The website is deployed via <strong>GitHub Pages</strong>:
                    <br>
                    <a href="https://elisa701.github.io/F1-Project/" target="_blank">
                        https://elisa701.github.io/F1-Project/
                    </a>
                </p>
            </section>

            <section>
                <h2>2. Technologies and tools</h2>
                <p><span class="pill pill--accent">HTML5</span><span class="pill pill--accent">CSS3</span></p>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>HTML5</strong> for semantic structure and content organization.</li>
                    <li><strong>CSS3</strong> for layout, typography, colors and responsive behavior.</li>
                    <li><strong>Flexbox</strong> and/or <strong>CSS Grid</strong> for page layout and cards.</li>
                    <li><strong>Git</strong> and <strong>GitHub</strong> for version control and hosting.</li>
                    <li><strong>GitHub Pages</strong> for free static deployment.</li>
                </ul>
            </section>

            <section>
                <h2>3. Site structure</h2>
                <h3>3.1 Main pages</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>index.html</strong> – homepage with general introduction to Formula 1.</li>
                    <li><strong>teams</strong> pages – cards for each team with logo, colors and basic info.</li>
                    <li><strong>drivers</strong> pages – profiles with photo, team, number and short bio.</li>
                    <li><strong>principals</strong> or staff pages – key figures with role and team.</li>
                </ul>

                <h3>3.2 Navigation</h3>
                <p>
                    A consistent <strong>navigation bar</strong> is reused across pages to allow the user to move
                    between teams, drivers and other sections.  
                    The active page is visually highlighted to improve orientation.
                </p>
            </section>

            <section>
                <h2>4. Layout and styling</h2>
                <h3>4.1 Global layout</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Use of a <strong>main container</strong> with max-width to keep content centered.</li>
                    <li>Consistent <strong>header</strong>, <strong>main</strong> and <strong>footer</strong> structure.</li>
                    <li>Cards for teams and drivers with images, titles and key data.</li>
                </ul>

                <h3>4.2 Responsive design</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Fluid widths and relative units (%, rem) where appropriate.</li>
                    <li>Media queries to adapt the number of columns on smaller screens.</li>
                    <li>Navigation and cards remain readable on mobile devices.</li>
                </ul>
            </section>
        </div>

        <!-- RIGHT COLUMN -->
        <div>
            <section>
                <h2>5. Code organization</h2>
                <h3>5.1 Repository</h3>
                <p>
                    The source code is stored on GitHub:
                    <br>
                    <a href="https://github.com/elisa701/F1-Project" target="_blank">
                        https://github.com/elisa701/F1-Project
                    </a>
                </p>
                <p>Example of a simple, reusable card structure:</p>
                <div class="code">
&lt;article class="team-card"&gt;
    &lt;img src="images/redbull.png" alt="Red Bull Racing logo"&gt;
    &lt;h2&gt;Red Bull Racing&lt;/h2&gt;
    &lt;p&gt;Drivers: Max Verstappen, Sergio Pérez&lt;/p&gt;
    &lt;a href="redbull.html" class="btn"&gt;Discover more&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/article&gt;
                </div>
            </section>

            <section>
                <h2>6. Accessibility and semantics</h2>
                <ul>
                    <li>Use of semantic tags: <code>&lt;header&gt;</code>, <code>&lt;nav&gt;</code>, <code>&lt;main&gt;</code>, <code>&lt;section&gt;</code>, <code>&lt;footer&gt;</code>.</li>
                    <li>Descriptive <strong>alt</strong> attributes for images (team logos, driver photos).</li>
                    <li>Clear heading hierarchy (<code>h1</code>, <code>h2</code>, <code>h3</code>).</li>
                    <li>Color contrast chosen to keep text readable on dark backgrounds.</li>
                </ul>
            </section>

            <section>
                <h2>7. Git and deployment workflow</h2>
                <ul>
                    <li>Local changes committed with meaningful messages (e.g. <code>"Add driver cards layout"</code>).</li>
                    <li>Push to GitHub to keep the remote repository updated.</li>
                    <li>GitHub Pages automatically serves the content from the <code>main</code> branch.</li>
                </ul>
                <p>
                    This workflow ensures that every change to the project is versioned and that the online
                    site is always synchronized with the repository.
                </p>
            </section>

            <section>
                <h2>8. Possible improvements</h2>
                <ul>
                    <li>Add simple <strong>animations</strong> or <strong>hover effects</strong> to cards and buttons.</li>
                    <li>Introduce a <strong>dark/light theme switcher</strong>.</li>
                    <li>Extend content with more detailed statistics for teams and drivers.</li>
                    <li>Refactor CSS into smaller, modular files for larger projects.</li>
                </ul>
                <p>
                    These improvements are not required for the assignment, but show how the project could evolve
                    into a richer Formula 1 information website.
                </p>
            </section>
        </div>
    </div>

    <footer>
        Technical presentation for the F1 Project – static website built with HTML &amp; CSS.
    </footer>
</div>
</body>
</html>
